def: A line connecting the points on the surface of the earth wherea certain temperature is found at the same depth.
In a peculiar manner; particulary; in a rare and strikingdegree; unusually.

A portion of the floor of a room raised above the generallevel, as a place for a bed or a throne; a platform; a dais.He [the teacher] himself should have his desk on a mounted estrade orplatform. J. G. Fitch.
A genus of marsipobranchs, including the hagfish. See Hag, 4.
Of or pertaining to the epigenesis; produced according to thetheory of epigenesis.
A kind of turnip commonly with a large and long or ovoidyellowish root; a Swedish turnip. See Turnip.
To join; to couple. [R.]The Englishmen accoupled themselves with the Frenchmen. Hall.
The tanning or dressing of leather. [Obs.] Blount.
Of or pertaining to the upper lip, or mustache.
A diseased condition produced by slow poisoning with arsenic.
